HEADWORD: Foreclosure
<hw>Fore*clo"sure</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or
process of foreclosing; a proceeding which bars or extinguishes a
mortgager's right of redeeming a mortgaged estate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

